There is created and established within the Finance and Administration Cabinet a Kentucky Gas Pipeline Authority composed of the following nine (9) members:
The secretary of the Finance and Administration Cabinet or his or her designee;
The secretary of the Tourism, Arts and Heritage Cabinet or his or her designee;
The secretary of the Energy and Environment Cabinet or his or her designee;
A member designated by the Kentucky Oil and Gas Association;
A member designated by the Kentucky Society of Professional Engineers who shall have experience in oil and gas pipeline construction;
A member designated by the Kentucky Gas Association representing a natural gas distribution company with a minimum annual throughput of ten billion (10,000,000,000) cubic feet;
A citizen member appointed by the Governor; and
Two (2) nonvoting legislator members, one (1) appointed by the President of the Senate and one (1) by the Speaker of the House of Representatives.
